        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 3:46PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 346 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles south of Holloman Air Force Base, moving south
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boles Acres.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 182 and 186.
Highway 54 in New Mexico between mile markers 36 and 56.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
